<h3><big>Canadian Brain Imaging Research Network (CBRAIN)</big></h3>

<h3>Funded by Canada's Advanced Network (CANARIE)</h3>

<p>The goal of CBRAIN is to develop a platform for distributed processing and exchange of 3D/4D brain imaging data. The expected result is a middleware platform that will render the processing environment (hardware, operating system, etc.) transparent to a remote user allowing them to apply complex algorithmic pipelines to large datasets stored at remote locations and to visualize the results as 3D maps in real time. This platform will provide a standard methodology for Canadian brain imaging researchers to collaborate productively and fully use available computing and networking resources.  This will increase the productivity and ease of collaboration among Canadian researchers leading to greater competitiveness with foreign researchers and improved medical research efficiency, ultimately leading to an improved quality of life across Canada. Though the focus of CBRAIN is providing tools for use by brain imaging researchers, the platform will be generalizable to other imaging domains, such as radiology, surgical planning and heart imaging, with profound consequences for Canadian medical research. (<%= link_to "More Information", about_us_path %>)</p>


